Introduction:
=============

This script generator makes sure to create standard script template & lib template
for creating new scripts. It makes sure to check on script naming convention 
adopted by crypto-devtest , it also makes sure to self induce author's name
as well as the testplan EDCS number.


Error conditions:
=================

1. It needs at least the executing script name( CryptoScriptGen ) and to be
generated script name ( e.g. fn_DGVPN_123456 ). If this condition is not met
you would see the following error.

[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>CryptoScriptGen

*****************************************************************

ERROR:Invalid Number of Args
 
INFO:USAGE: CryptoScriptGen <script> [path]


*****************************************************************
[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>



2. It tries to determine if the script name to be generated follows standard.
You would see the following error if the name does not confirm.
The script name standard is [test_type]_<feature name>_<EDCS no>

a. Here we just gave try as the script name.
====================================================



[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>CryptoScriptGen try

*****************************************************************

INFO:The scriptname args:  1stvalue = try , 2ndvalue = , 3rdvalue =  

*****************************************************************

!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

INFO:You are making this as a regular script,  if you know ur script type

INFO:Please use <test type>_<feature name>_ <EDCS No>_[Section]_[Subsection]

INFO:Feature name is being determined as try

*****************************************************************

ERROR:EDCS no is not found at 

INFO:Since ur script is generic, please use  <feature name>_<EDCS No>_...format 


*****************************************************************
[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>



b. Here we give A12345 as EDCS no.
======================================



[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>CryptoScriptGen GETVPN_A12345

*****************************************************************

INFO:The scriptname args:  1stvalue = GETVPN , 2ndvalue = A12345, 3rdvalue =  

*****************************************************************

!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

INFO:You are making this as a regular script,  if you know ur script type

INFO:Please use <test type>_<feature name>_ <EDCS No>_[Section]_[Subsection]

INFO:Feature name is being determined as GETVPN

*****************************************************************

ERROR:EDCS no is not found at A12345

INFO:Since ur script is generic, please use  <feature name>_<EDCS No>_...format 


*****************************************************************
[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>




c. We give the name that already exists.
========================================== 
[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>CryptoScriptGen DGVPN_123456 

*****************************************************************

INFO:The scriptname args:  1stvalue = DGVPN , 2ndvalue = 123456, 3rdvalue =  

*****************************************************************

!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

INFO:You are making this as a regular script,  if you know ur script type

INFO:Please use <test type>_<feature name>_ <EDCS No>_[Section]_[Subsection]

INFO:Feature name is being determined as DGVPN

*****************************************************************

INFO:EDCS no found , number is 123456 

*****************************************************************

ERROR: File ./DGVPN_123456 or ./DGVPN_123456.exp exists
, please remove before running CryptoScriptGen 

*****************************************************************
[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>




d. We give test_type but miss feature_type.
=============================================



[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>CryptoScriptGen fn_123456

*****************************************************************

INFO:The scriptname args:  1stvalue = fn , 2ndvalue = 123456, 3rdvalue =  

*****************************************************************

INFO:Your Script type is being determined as functional

*****************************************************************

ERROR:EDCS no is not found at  

INFO:Since ur script is not generic, please use  <test type>_<feature name>...format

*****************************************************************
[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>




e. We give test_type, but mess up EDCS no.
===========================================

[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>CryptoScriptGen fn_GETVPN_ppp

*****************************************************************

INFO:The scriptname args:  1stvalue = fn , 2ndvalue = GETVPN, 3rdvalue = ppp 

*****************************************************************

INFO:Your Script type is being determined as functional

*****************************************************************

ERROR:EDCS no is not found at ppp 

INFO:Since ur script is not generic, please use  <test type>_<feature name>...format

*****************************************************************
[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>
 

3. Once we give everything correct, it creates two files.



*****************************************************************
[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>CryptoScriptGen fn_GETVPN_123456

*****************************************************************

INFO:The scriptname args:  1stvalue = fn , 2ndvalue = GETVPN, 3rdvalue = 123456 

*****************************************************************

INFO:Your Script type is being determined as functional

*****************************************************************

INFO:EDCS no found , number is 123456

*****************************************************************
Created the files:
./fn_GETVPN_123456
./fn_GETVPN_123456.exp
[inasingh-u5:/auto/stg-devtest/inasingh/stg_reg/utils]>


4. Open the file, you should see ur name as authors & EDCS-number
 for testplan and script name filled in already.

# Name:
#     fn_GETVPN_123456
#

# Author:
#     inasingh -- (inasingh@cisco.com)
#

# References:
#     Add the EDCS title and Number here of the test plan(s) & functional spec
#     that the script covers.
#     Testplan:  EDCS-123456


If you have any other questions, please e-mail inasingh@cisco.com 
or crypto-devtest@cisco.com
 
